The paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a state-of-the-art relation extraction model and attention mechanism suggests that the paper also involves machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG) techniques. The analysis of the attention mechanism and the use of novel metrics indicate that the paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV) subfields.
